font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwulongm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WulongM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 1:59:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Vex Thal KEY!</span><hr size=1> Alright, so far we know that there are 10 silver links needed to do this quest.  The &quot;amulet&quot;, which is a 10 slot bag, is obtainable in Umbral Plains from the Remains of Vah Kerrath.  Whisperlings have something to do with this, and Whisperling faction as well.  So far there is no known location of any silver link nor the existence of them, other than the Remains of Vah Kerrath stating that they already exist.  To me, this means they're found on the ground or dropped from an enemy.  There have been a few good ideas I have seen though.  There are 10 stones that drop in Umbral Plains, total.  New stones, nobody has seen them before from what I know.  Maybe an enchanter could try JCing an enchanted silver bar w/the stones, and try combining them together.  Well, post further thoughts here, that other thread is totally fux0red and it's getting ridiculous.  Please only post information here, don't let this post get out of hand as the other one did..... just a simple request. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaisersoze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaiserSoze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 4:40:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vex Thal KEY!</span><hr size=1> More than 10 of those new stones, drop in other zones too, its for the new jewelcraft that didn't get implemented because they're still trying to figure out what to do with it, and its way old news, sorry to burst your bubble, but you're way off course. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mirk>Mirk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 6:21:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> heh</span><hr size=1> My money is on unimplemented quest, unfinished zone. They're probably seeing how people handle the new stuff in luclin and busily trying to figure out how to make it more effective in killing ya, so they can stick that in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucuellar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuellar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 6:55:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> I say they have they're goign to put it on legends first. : P<br><br>Then they will transfer the zone to the normal servers.   <br><br>You will then be required to enter your credit card number to purchase each of the 10 links (letting multiple people pay the $1000 enterance fee, so they had 10 links instead of 1).  You will then be able to use the key, and receive a tour of Vex thall at a charge of $4 per person on the raid from Abashi. <br><br>-Cuellar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulimbas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>limbas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 7:36:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> Some people in Inner Circle on Xegony have claimed to have a key already, who knows.  I say nay, but maybe they are smarter than I 8p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwulongm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WulongM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 8:19:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> Hrm..... was just a thought, figures they'd throw Luclin at us incomplete though.  I'll go with incomplete quest, but I'm not too sure about incomplete zone, there was a patch for Vex Thal not too long ago, /shrug.  I don't know what they're doing with the quest and if anyone finds out anything about the 10 links, it will probably be in a larger guild on any given server, which will mean it won't get posted here for sure.  Ahh well, will keep checking back for updates, etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stbb>St BB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/22/02 8:41:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> Get off the &quot;Legends Sux&quot; bandwagon, all the &quot;Loot for $$&quot; jokes are old and tired now. Vex Thal is in game. Has it been solved? I really don't know. But the zone is there waiting with all it's weirdness. <br><br>I just wish all the legends bashers would grow up and get some sense. It is a premium service. You get what you pay for. I don't see people in coach complaining that the people in first class don't deserve their champagne and big seats just because they pay more. But, of course they are still bitter. I guess that's where the anti legends crowd is coming from. Jealousy of those who want to spend more to get more.  <br><br>Oh! Just thought of an even better example for all the spoiled internet people. Imagine everyone with dial up complaining that they deserved broadband for the same price they pay for dial up. Because they were promised fast downloads and broadband is faster so why should people who pay more get something they should have had in the first place...it boggles the mind. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulechevalierblanc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Le Chevalier Blanc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/02 2:24:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> I can say with 100% certainty that Vex Thal is at least up and running with mobs, zone architecture, and pathing.  I have a friend who is a guide that popped in there for a moment to take a look around.  Dunno about drops since nothing was killed, but it looked like a fully functional zone from all angles not involving combat.<br><br>-Le Chevalier Blanc<br>Barbarian Assassin of 60 winters, Erollisi Marr<br><br>P.S. Don't ask for more info - turns out they put out a memo banning guides from going in there just a few days afterwards. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uniamdsparil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Niam DSparil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/02 2:56:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> I believe most of the negative Legends energy comes from the fact that (a) there is a lot of broken stuff in the game, (b) the GM service promised on Legends was promised in EQ, and (c) overall money being spent on Legends 'premium' customers and ignoring the mass of people who made everyone at VI so much money.<br><br>Does it upset me that people paying 4 times the amount of money I am get such better service?  No.  What really irritates me is that $10 a month I pay should be getting me that service already.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukenuvan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kenuvan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/02 2:58:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> wrong</span><hr size=1> no person from inner circle on xegony has the key =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyaedar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaedar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/02 3:07:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> Well I can tell you all and I have got this info from a few GMs and a developer... Yes Vex Thal is up but No not all items are in the game yet for the quest. Oh and the person that said the items would most likely go to Legends first is right.<br><br>Oh and any guild or person that says they have the Vex Thal key just tell them good luck in there and that you and your guild have the new Uber key to the new Crushbone zone thats under the castle and that you have already had a bp drop with 150 AC on it.<br><br>The items for the 10 silver links will be put onto Legends first as they will test out a few things on legends and then send them to the regular servers. Plus Verant will use that to get more people to Legends by using the Vex Thal key to get people to maybe change to premium server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujuggurnaut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juggurnaut</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/02 7:01:30 am)</font><br>   <a 