=title> Re: This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> During a raid in the Umbral Plains one of my guildmates went linkdead along the zone wall to the right of the ME zoneline.  He logged back in under the world and when he moved he was teleported behind the locked door.  The same thing that happens in the netherbian lair at that unknown zoneline that knocks you back happened to him here.  Every time he tried to walk towards the zoneline, he was placed back a few feet.  So... it is probably not worth wasting the time surmising about how to jewelcraft the key or other foolishness, the zone may be &quot;ready&quot; or it may not be, but VI doesnt want people entering it yet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvowelumos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vowelumos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 6:27:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> Why the seriously paranoid anti-legends crowds needs to stop making stuff up.  It is ridiculous.  Can we please ahve a thread on these boards about anything where some moron does not mention legends.  Can we perhaps starting getting this garbage removed.  It is starting to be like the &quot;Monk Item&quot; posts that flooded allakahzam's site not too long ago.  <br><br>BTW I love all of the people with GM/Guide &quot;Friends&quot; who are not good enough friends to not brag about their &quot;friends&quot; doing things they are not supposed to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uadairenbots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adairen BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 7:25:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> ST BB,<br><br>You are missing the point you moron.<br><br>People are complaining about legends because of the fact that the 'regular' 10$ subscriber is getting shafted for the service they were expected to recieve.<br><br>Let me show you, in your little example you demonstrated.<br><br>Coach class and 1st Class are very different. Imagine there was no first class and what if the airlines you were flying with promised leather chairs , champagne and all the other high class crap for the price of coach. But in turn, they never provided you with that service, and now, they opened up a new section called 1st Class. For a new price (4x as much as coach), leather chairs, champagne and everything else would be provided.<br><br>People could care less whos on the Legends server. The reason people have some fury on the subject is due to Verants inability provide good service for the loyal and patient customers that have been waiting on the '1st Class' service they were promised, for the 'Coach' price. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uadairenbots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adairen BotS</A> at: 2/24/02 7:27:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzamtin00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zamtin00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 7:58:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This isn't funny anymore.</span><hr size=1> I've been behind that door at Vex Thal also and yea you do get knocked back a few feet when you hit zone line, but I think the door itself IS the zone in. If it wasn't 1 key would open the door and let 2000 people inside which doesn't sound like Verant for their special keyed uber dungeon of Luclin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyanbun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yanbun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 9:40:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> r</span><hr size=1> Its a typical human nature thing. We have problems? Hey look, something to blame it on!<br><br>Guys, Legends isnt going to effect the casual gamer. Stop bitching about it and worry about your own problems.<br><br>I am sick of people blaming everything on legends. Ever since I annoucned on the Mage board I was moving to legends, and would answer any questions people had about the server, I've gotten 93 pieces of complaints, hate mail, or just plan spam. Give it up guys, go do something productive. <br><br>Sorry for the rant, but COME ON guys, its old. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stbb>St BB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/02 11:35:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Apologies for the hijacking this even more.</span><hr size=1> Before I even begin my reply to Adairen (I'm assuming the BotS means you're in Blood of the Spider, so I'm going to assume you have a decent amount of knowledge about the game), I would like to apologise to the mods and other posters for derailing this even more. <br><br>To hopefully mitigate that I will add something about Vex Thal. To the person who mentioned the area behind the door that just pushes you back. That is so people cannot exploit the door as has been done in other zones SSRA for example. (ie you camp against it and come back a few times till you warp through). The door is not the zone. There is a zone line back there that requires you to have the key in order to zone and not get knocked back. This also answers a  question. <br>Q: Will a guild just need 1 key to get in?<br>A: Nope a key will open the door, but everyone will need one to zone in.<br><br>Now that I've said something about Vex Thal, maybe this response will be that much of a derailment (A penny on the track instead of a cow. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br><br>OK Adairen. Gonna just ignore the moron comment. I don't take issue with that crap, par for the course if you post on a message board.<br><br>Just gonna respond to your oh so well made comments.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> People are complaining about legends because of the fact that the 'regular' 10$ subscriber is getting shafted for the service they were expected to recieve.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>What do you mean by service they were expected (sic) to recieve? You get customer service, every server has guides and GMs that provide it on server, as well as email and a phone number. I can't think of anyplace that says specifically how much service you get, ie. there is no statement that says &quot;All petitions will be answered within 10 min&quot; or something along those lines. I mean come on. Think about this. You pay $10 a month that's $120 a year know how much that comes out to per day? About $0.34. Please oh please tell me what you can expect to get for $0.34, even those save the children commercials want $0.75 a day. I'm even gonna break it down to the hour. It's less than 2 cents! I think the cost of electricity and phone needed to play the game costs more than that per hour. So give me a break about the quality of service.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Coach class and 1st Class are very different. Imagine there was no first class and what if the airlines you were flying with promised leather chairs , champagne and all the other high class crap for the price of coach. But in turn, they never provided you with that service, and now, they opened up a new section called 1st Class. For a new price (4x as much as coach), leather chairs, champagne and everything else would be provided.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>What promise? Where? I guess I am a moron since I don't see anything on the website or my EULA that &quot;Promises&quot; any exact level of service. The only thing that is promised is that service exists, that it is there and that you have access to it. Same deal with quests. Quests are in game, dynamic events are run. There is no mention of how often these things will be done. VI has not, to my knowledge ever promised us what they are now about to provide to legends. The difference is this, they are saying EXPLICITLY what they will be providing to Legends. While what we are promised is general and everyone on the anti-Legends bandwagon just decided that since they haven't been told specifically what level of service they should get they would just make assumptions on what they FEEL they should have or should get for their $0.34 a day.<br><br>So unless I missed something in your post I think I hit the point dead on.<br><br>Tyrvidar Brightblade 55 Warrior<br>Bonebristle Brightblade 51 Paladin<br>Patron Saints<br>Fennin Ro<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=4196.topic&start=21&stop=33>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=4196.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=4196.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4196.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=4196.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=4196.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4196.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4196.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquest